{"questionId":"22457285","questionHtml":"<p>Show that, according to the model, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>40</mn><mo> </mo><mn>000</mn></mrow><mi>x</mi></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>800</mn><mo> </mo><mn>000</mn></mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p>profit for each smoothie&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>20</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong><em>(M1)</em></strong></p>\n<p><strong><em><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>40</mn><mo> </mo><mn>000</mn></mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac><mo>×</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>20</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; A1</em></strong></p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p>profit <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo></math> revenue&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo></math> costs <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mi>n</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>20</mn><mi>n</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>×</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>40</mn><mo> </mo><mn>000</mn></mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mn>20</mn><mo>×</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>40</mn><mo> </mo><mn>000</mn></mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Do not award <strong><em>A1</em></strong> if <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>40</mn><mo> </mo><mn>000</mn></mrow><mi>x</mi></mfrac></math> seen as first term unless explained (in part (a) or (b)), as it is given in question.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;